            <div class="ins_notes">
                <span class="note" id="note-1"><a href="#ref-1">[1]</a> Decree 1 is a decree of the Athenian People of 279 BC, decree 2 was passed slightly earlier by the Athenian cleruchy in Hephaistia on Lemnos, decree 3, also passed by the cleruchs, relates to Komeas' service on an embassy to Seleukos in summer of 281 BC.</span>
<span class="note" id="note-2"><a href="#ref-2">[2]</a> A fragment of the second stele here mentioned survives as <a class="highlight" href="/inscription/IGII31/885"><i>IG</i> II<sup>3</sup> 1, 885</a>.</span>
